Vision and Strategy
 A PSC guides client through a 60-90-minute meeting to discover key company priorities, HR priorities, and culture elements to establish program objectives/goals and inform program design activities across all software elements. This is done on a yearly basis as needed and program objectives are reviewed during Partnership Review meetings.
 Design Support
 A PSC provides clients with recommendations on content and configuration design (questionnaire, cadence, audience, etc.) for up to 3 programs (I.e., Engage, Onboarding, 360, Feedback, etc.) each year depending on the software purchased.
 Insight Reviews
 A PSC provides clients with an org level results presentation highlighting: engagement performance, response rate, comment topics, key drivers, recommended focus areas, and suggested actions. Each year a client will receive two insight-review presentations. Insight Reviews are intended for the executive/leadership team and are primarily slide format using the Glint Platform as a supplement, these presentations may incorporate results from multiple programs/software to show connections between programs (Cross Program Insights) depending on purchased software. Prior to each Insight Review Glint and client will align on research questions to explore and provide a preview of the presentation prior to presenting to the executive team. 
 Analytics Feasibility Study  
 Upon request no more than once a year, the Glint People Science team will meet with the customer in a discovery meeting to determine the plausibility of performing an advanced analytics project such as linkage or custom reporting outside of the Glint platform. If useful insights seem likely, Glint will make a recommendation for such an analytics project that will meet the customer’s needs.
 Partnership Support (GPR)
 Your PSC participates in bi-annual/quarterly reviews of the partnership to confirm/update/modify program objectives and identify ways to improve the overall relationship.

An assigned CSM will be appointed as customer’s strategic partner and customer advocate responsible for overall program management, platform optimization, best practices, and coaching. Glint-led administration across all products purchased on behalf of the customer. In addition, Assigned Customer Success Manager and Technical Success Manager will lead the implementation, including but not limited to project management, best practices, and configuring products purchased using Glint best practices tailored to customer's needs.

Glint will partner with you to help bring people success behaviors to your organization. Our goal in working together is to equip and empower you to drive transformation and successfully manage your own people success programs moving forward. In this package a People Science Consultant (PSC) will work with you as a thought partner in helping to develop a vision for your people success program(s). Based on your strategic priorities and Glint's research, we will advise you on the design of your People Success program(s). Once your survey closes, together we will explore the insights in your platform, show you how you can use the platform to find your own insights moving forward, and enable you to take action on your results. Your package will include a People Science Consultant to lead three meetings: (1) Strategy & Design meeting [60-minute meeting], (1) Live Platform Exploration meeting [60-minute meeting], and (1) Transformation Continuation meeting [60-minute meeting].

This option is intended to provide additional support for specific services (see table of services) beyond what is provided in a clients’ People Science Package. It is a prerequisite to have current People Science Package.

Scheduled recurring, ad-hoc & always-on Surveys to measure employee engagement, team effectiveness, or manager effectiveness. Includes Standard Support, up to 5 Named System Administrators, & OnDemandSurveys.

Glint Feedback and Conversations enables employees to request, provide, and take action on development feedback using Anytime Feedback & Recognition and Development Goals modules. Customers with this SKU will also have access to any future features

Automatically triggered Surveys that are triggered by a set period of time after an event like onboarding, promotion, role change, and/or end of employment/exit. Includes Standard Support, up to 5 Named System Admins, and OnDemandSurveys.

The Glint 360s Module is a multi-rater employee feedback tool intended to enable employees to obtain a holistic review of their strengths and growth opportunities based on input from peers, collaborators, direct reports and managers (such reviews, ?360 Reviews?). This Module is intended to enable human resources professionals to quickly initiate 360 Reviews for Customer employees and to provide the employees with actionable feedback following the completion of the 360 Reviews.

This bundle includes scheduled recurring, ad-hoc & always-on Surveys to measure employee engagement, team effectiveness, manager effectiveness, and/or diversity & inclusion, plus automatically triggered Surveys that are triggered by a set period of time after an event like onboarding, promotion, role change, and/or end of employment/exit. Includes Standard Support, up to 5 Named System Admins, and OnDemandSurveys.

People Success is a product bundle with access to all Glint product features to measure and deliver insight into the employee experience, launch development feedback programs, and provide suggested actions and learning. This bundle includes Glint’s Engage, Lifecycle, 360s, Anytime Feedback & Recognition, and Development Goals modules, as well as any future features. Includes Standard Support, up to 5 Named System Admins, and OnDemandSurveys.

Apply with LinkedIn (AWLI) is a a plugin that customers can implement on their external career site, which enables candidates to apply using their LinkedIn profile information. Applicant data is sent directly to the ATS, and Apply Starters are also surfaced in Spotlights in LinkedIn Recruiter.
